<item>
            <title>[FLINK-4696] Limit the number of Akka Dispatcher Threads in LocalMiniCluster</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-4696</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;By default, akka spawns 2x or 3x the number of cores in threads.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For the LocalFlinkMiniCluster, running on Travis (often 64 cores), with separate actor systems for jobmanager and multiple taskmanagers, this frequetly means &amp;gt;600 akka threads. Flink uses about 4 actors.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This simply eats unnecessary resources. I suggest to have at most 4 threads per actor system in test setups.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
